article.headline: Yale 71, Hampton 52
article.story: NEW HAVEN, Conn. (AP) -- Eric Flato had a career-high 20 points to lead Yale to a 71-52 win over Hampton on Sunday. The sophomore point guard was 7-of-10 from the field, including 5-of-6 on 3-point attempts. Dominick Martin added 14 points and five rebounds in 17 minutes for Yale (4-4). Martin made 7-of-11 shots. Yale used a 20-8 run to open the second half to go ahead 53-33 with 9:07 left to play. Matt Kyle had a career-high nine points and five rebounds for the Bulldogs, who led by as many as 23 in the second half. Rodrick Coleman had 16 points to lead Hampton (1-5). Coleman, a transfer from St. Louis Community College-Forest Park, was playing in his first game of the season. Bruce Brown, Hampton's 6-11 center and Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference preseason player of the year, was held to eight points, five below his average. Six of his points came in the final nine minutes. Yale built a 29-14 lead in the first half, but Hampton closed the final 5:07 with an 11-4 run to pull within 33-25 at the break.
